description._content: Catalog #: 09_01268 Title: Captain Dorris Dimmock Gurley Special Collection Photo Honolulu Hawaii Additional Information: Six pilots in flight gear, Honolulu 1926. Handwritten inscription ""Just prior to flight order"", Dorris Gurley joined the U.S. Navy in 1919 aged 25. His active naval service finished in April 1946, when he retired with the rank of Captain. During World War II he commanded the naval air stations at Ottumwa, Iowa and later at Bunker Hill, Indiana, Tags: Captain Dorris Dimmock Gurley Special Collection Photo Honolulu Hawaii,Â 1926 Repository: San Diego Air and Space Museum Archive
